choices.text:
some people around me justify political choices based on the music they listen to. Cos if you’re not a Gang starr, Bubasoft, Anyone against the police is a cop in underground Hip Hop circles, especially of our city. This is truly a problem in Madagascar, politicised Hip Hop, somewhat the reason there’s no big hip hop artists other than just a handful. Because those boys are worried about the rap game, over-thinking the music instead of making music and doing what they love. Looks like it’s a alugh, but people here view hip hop, not for the love of the art, but for the division linked to it.

As a white half counselor in the U.S., my first task of the campaign is crushed.

In the 1980s, we wanted to show people in 'democratic' countries what life was for black people.

But criticisms of the author and the genre ignore that there were black and brown people involved in every part of the industry.
